<div>The current email system on campus allows employees 500MB space.  Here's how to tell how close you are to the limit:</div>
<div></div>
<h2>In Outlook 2010:</h2>
<ol>
<li>Right-click your Mailbox</li>
<li>Data File Properties...</li>
<li>Folder Size...</li>
</ol>
<h2>On the Web:</h2>
<ol>
<li>Log-in to <a href="http://my.byui.edu/">my.byui.edu</a><span style="text-align: left; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: italic; line-height: normal; font-size: small;">.</span></li>
<li style="text-align: left;">Under the <strong>Administrative Items</strong>next to your E-mail link you will see the percentage of space used. </li>
<li style="text-align: left;">To determine which folders are using the most space, click the percentage link.</li>
</ol>
